From: ROCKNIX
Add Adreno 830 (gen8_0_0) chip-id variants to Turnip / freedreno.

Mesa 26.1.2 ships the base a830 id (0xffff44050000), but not the rev-0001 or
KGSL forms. Ported from ROCKNIX (projects/ROCKNIX/packages/graphics/mesa/
patches/SM8750/0001-add-a830-chip-id.patch). Pairs with the kernel
sm8750-adreno-a830-gpu-driver.patch.
--- a/src/freedreno/common/freedreno_devices.py
+++ b/src/freedreno/common/freedreno_devices.py
@@ -1342,7 +1342,9 @@

 add_gpus([
         GPUId(chip_id=0xffff44050000, name="Adreno (TM) 830"),
-        GPUId(chip_id=0x44050001, name="Adreno (TM) 830"), # KGSL
+        GPUId(chip_id=0xffff44050001, name="Adreno (TM) 830"),
+        GPUId(chip_id=0x44050000, name="Adreno (TM) 830"), # KGSL
+        GPUId(chip_id=0x44050001, name="Adreno (TM) 830"), # KGSL 0001
     ], A6xxGPUInfo(
         CHIP.A8XX,
         [a7xx_base, a7xx_gen3, a8xx_base, a8xx_gen1],
